description:
TnPort table describes Transport Network port information for a specific RAN site.

- dateTime: Timestamp indicating when the data was recorded.
- Area_Name: Name of the geographical area (e.g., NR_Balikpapan).
- CellId: Identifier of the cell site.
- Id2: Redundant identifier, seemingly mirroring CellId.
- Id3:  An arbitrary identifier, likely internal.
- Id4:  A simplified identifier for the transport network port.
- vsDataType: Data type identifier, specifying this data as related to Transport Network ports.
- vsDataFormatVersion: Version of the data format used.
- TnPort.userLabel: User-defined label for the port (currently empty).
- TnPort.sfpModuleRef: Reference to the SFP module the port belongs to, including hierarchical network identifiers.
- TnPort.reservedBy: Reference to the network element that has reserved the port, using hierarchical identifiers.
- TnPort.channelRef: Reference to the specific channel within the SFP module, using hierarchical identifiers.
- TnPort.tnPortId: Unique identifier for the transport network port.
